  "difficulty_guidance": {
    "easy": "Single procedure, single diagnosis. Very common scenario (e.g., cholecystectomy for gallstones, cataract extraction). CPT code is one well-known code. ICD-10 is a 3-4 character code requiring minimal specificity. No modifiers required.",
    "medium": "Slightly less common procedure, or requires one modifier, or diagnosis requires 5-character specificity. Example: distinguishing STEMI vs NSTEMI, or adding -LT/-RT laterality modifier.",
    "hard": "Multiple procedures in one encounter (e.g., colonoscopy with polypectomy PLUS biopsy), requires modifier -59 for separate procedures, bilateral designation (-50), or full 7-character ICD-10 code. May involve bundling rules the student must know to unbundle correctly."
  }
